          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ContractLineDelete",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete a contract line from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.ContractLine",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table in a Microsoft SQL Server database. It also updates related tables and logs the operation. The procedure ensures that the contract line is not associated with any invoices before deletion. If the deletion is successful, it updates the contract's financial amounts and logs the operation. If an error occurs, it rolls back the transaction and logs the error details."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
